article.headline: Lipscomb 67, Evansville 64
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Trey Williams hit a 3-pointer and two key free throws down the stretch to lead Lipscomb to a 67-64 comeback victory Monday night over Evansville. Williams' 3-pointer with 1:50 left cut Evansville's lead to 64-63, and he made two free throws with 1:11 left to push the Bisons (2-0) ahead for good 65-64. Lipscomb's Eddie Ard made two free throws with 4 seconds left for the final points of the game. Ard finished with 21 points, Williams had 20 and Brian Fisk scored 10. The Purple Aces (0-1) led the entire second half, except for a 37-all tie, until Williams' free throws. Evansville's biggest lead was 50-41 on a Darin Granger jumper with 10:41 left. Jason Holsinger led the Purple Aces with 15 points and Matt Webster had 13. Evansville did not score a field goal in the last 3:02.
